The paper deals with compressive imaging, which involves reconstructing images from a reduced number of linear measurements. This is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), machine learning (cs.LG), and signal processing (cs.SP). Given that the paper proposes algorithms for image reconstruction and denoising, it is likely to be relevant to at least some of these sub-fields.
